  "_comment": "Compat-sync map. Source path → required compat.json prefix(es) + doc(s) + test(s). When a diff touches any path matching a key, the corresponding requirement(s) must be satisfied in the same diff (compat.json prefix entry populated + doc page touched + test glob matched), OR a `Compat-Update: skip prefix=<...> reason=\"...\"` trailer must appear on a commit in the range. Multiple skip lines allowed, one per prefix; bare `Compat-Update: skip` (no reason) is rejected.\n\nThe `*` prefix is a wildcard meaning the requirement applies regardless of which compat section the change touches — used when the source-path itself spans multiple sections (e.g. core/view/src/widget_bridge.cpp dispatches into css/, html/, canvas2d/ and rn/).\n\nNote: paired with tools/scripts/compat_sync_check.py and the populated compat.json aggregate at the repo root. Empty compat sections are scaffolds, not satisfied compatibility entries; add or update real matrix entries when a mapped source change affects support.\n\nFuture extension: the `@pulp/react` and `@pulp/css-adapt` paths from the issue body live in separate npm packages NOT in this repo. Add entries here when those packages move into the monorepo.",
